Copyright (c) 2026 sibyx. All rights reserved.

This license governs the SibyX software, including its source code, build/minified artifacts, documentation, user interface, and related assets (collectively, the "Software").

1. Definitions. "Commercial Purpose" means any use aimed at profit, commercial operation, paid services to businesses, or embedding in a commercial product, including but not limited to selling the Software, paid SaaS, bundling, ad monetization, or distributing it as part of a commercial product. "Attribution" means retaining the original copyright notice, prominently crediting SibyX and its source, and including this license (or a clear link to it).

2. Grant of Rights. Subject to the terms below, the copyright holder grants you the right to use, study, modify, and non-commercially reproduce and distribute the Software (including modified versions), provided that attribution and this license are retained.

3. Restrictions. Without prior written permission from sibyx, you may NOT: (a) use the Software for any Commercial Purpose; (b) remove, hide, or alter any copyright notice, attribution, or this license; (c) imply you are the original author of SibyX or claim any trademark rights.

4. Attribution. Any distribution or public display must retain the "Copyright (c) 2026 sibyx" notice, prominently credit SibyX and its source, and include this license or a clear link to it.

5. Trademark. The name "SibyX" and related marks are trademarks of sibyx. This license grants no trademark rights.

6. Disclaimer. The Software is provided "as is" without warranty of any kind, express or implied, including but not limited to warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, or non-infringement. In no event shall the copyright holder or contributors be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, or consequential damages arising from use of the Software.

7. Commercial Licensing. To use the Software commercially, obtain prior written permission from sibyx.

8. Termination. Rights terminate automatically upon any breach; you must then stop all use and distribution and destroy all copies.

